cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.OS, cs.CR, cs.PF 

This paper is about improving the performance of key-value (KV) stores, which are commonly used in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses data structures and algorithms used in KV stores, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper proposes a new design for KV stores that aims to improve performance under update-intensive workloads, which is related to operating systems (cs.OS) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing KV store designs, which could be considered as a critique (cs.CR).
